				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\begin{array}{*{20}{c}} {Q_{{\mathrm{prov}}} = 1.65/\tau _{{\mathrm{repeat}}}} \end{array}.$$\end{document}Qprov=1.65∕τrepeat.Thus, we find that a carbon flux capable of initiating the PETM is achieved with τrepeat between 2 and 6 years (Fig. 4e, f).

The mantle plume flux parameter is a fundamental measure of how fast temperature pulses move round a mantle convection cell. It can be directly linked to rates of mantle melting, and here we exploit this opportunity to estimate sill injection frequency. We express the sill intrusion recurrence period as 1/τrepeat = Qρ, where Q is the rate of expansion of sill province area and ρ is the number of sills per unit area of the seafloor (Methods). We postulate that the area of sill intrusion in the uppermost lithosphere ALIP is effectively the same as the area of magma generation at the base of the lithosphere, Amantle. This assumption is reasonable because basaltic magma can travel up through the plate to the surface on a timeframe comparable with PETM onset, or shorter41,42. If melting occurs across the entire footprint of the expanding patch of unusually hot mantle, then2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\begin{array}{*{20}{c}} {Q = \frac{{{\mathrm{{d}}}A_{{\mathrm{mantle}}}}}{{{\mathrm{{d}}}t}} = \frac{{{\mathrm{{d}}}A_{{\mathrm{LIP}}}}}{{{\mathrm{{d}}}t}}} \end{array}.$$\end{document}Q=dAmantledt=dALIPdt.Thus, Q can also be interpreted as the mantle plume area flux, the rate of areal expansion averaged vertically across the plume head. More generally, expansion of the sill province is smaller than Q because thicker lithosphere inhibits decompression melting in some places, so that ALIP < Amantle (Fig. 1). Incorporating this effect modifies the expression for τrepeat to3\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
